Here's a brand new show dedicated to Welsh football.
We hope it's the first in a regular series made by and for Welsh football fans.
Yes, there are post-match interviews with our elite stars and plenty of chat about our World Cup qualifying campaign.
But the Welsh football scene is so much more. 
So we'll be looking at the women's game, age grades and what's being done at the grass roots by The Welsh Football Trust to get young people involved. 
It's presented by the good people at Eatsleepfootyrepeat and produced by FOCUS SHIFT FILMS. And you'll find it here on our Facebook page.
Enjoy and please let us know what you think!

SPONSORED COMPETITION: What's your top tip for making family memories this summer?

Add your imaginative idea to Cadw's bucket-and-spade activity list and you could win a Lego experience for 10 or an iPad Mini!

Cadw's Pack your Imagination campaign is encouraging families to take part in inspired events at historic sites this summer - including building sandcastles at real castles, bouncing on inflatable fortresses and building Lego replicas.

To enter our competition, just look at Cadw's bucket-and-spade list of essential family activities here http://cadw.gov.wales/fun/packyourimagination/bucket-and-spade-list/?lang=en and tell us below what you would add. Remember, it has to link to Welsh history or a Cadw site!

The winner will be able to choose between a blockbusting experience for up to 10 children at a Lego Innovation Centre (in Aberbeeg or Rhyl) or a brand-new iPad Mini (16GB). Plus two runners-up will receive a Cadw Family membership.

Cadw is the Welsh Government's historic environment service.

The closing date for entries is 2pm on Thursday, July 30. UK residents and over 16s only. Terms and conditions apply. See www.walesonline.co.uk/rules and http://bit.ly/1LDer59 Remember to check back on Thursday to see if you're the winner!

Add your imaginative idea to Cadw's bucket-and-spade activity list and you could win a Lego experience for 10 or an iPad Mini!
 
Cadw's Pack your Imagination campaign is encouraging families to take part in inspired events at historic sites this summer - including building sandcastles at real castles, bouncing on inflatable fortresses and building Lego replicas.
 
To enter our competition, just look at Cadw's bucket-and-spade list of essential family activities here http://cadw.gov.wales/fun/packyourimagination/bucket-and-spade-list/?lang=en then tell us below what you would add. The winner will be able to choose between a blockbusting experience for up to 10 children at a Lego Innovation Centre (in Aberbeeg or Rhyl) or a brand-new iPad Mini (16GB). Plus two runners-up will receive a Cadw Family membership.
 
Cadw is the Welsh Government's historic environment service.

The closing date for entries is 2pm on Thursday, July 30. UK residents and over 16s only. Terms and conditions apply. See www.walesonline.co.uk/rules and http://bit.ly/1LDer59 Remember to check back on Thursday to see if you're the winner!

It's all part of its Pack your Imagination campaign, backed by Bob Carney, a castle enthusiast and Lego expert from Illinois, who creates replicas of medieval castles (including 13 Welsh structures) in his spare time.
Cadw is inviting families to enter the competition by submitting images or videos of their attempts at building replica castles.
Post your castle creations in the comments below by 30 April.

Plus there are six runner-up prizes of ¬£50 Lego vouchers.

STOP what you are doing. Because here is a story of a man so generous that it might just have you welling up.

Dan Black was paralysed in a cycling accident in 2009, and has since dreamed of walking again.

He raised ¬£20,000 for stem cell treatment in the hope he could walk again, but then he heard about the story of little five-year-old Brecon Vaughan (pictured with Dan), who has a rare condition that means he cannot walk unaided.

Dan Black gave the ¬£20,000 he raised to Brecon's family to help pay for expensive life-changing treatment for the five-year-old.

What a wonderful act of compassion from Dan, who in our eyes is an absolute hero. The world needs more people like Dan.

We're sure Dan didn't do this for recognition, or in the hope of lots of people reading about his kind act, but please pass this story of kindness onto your friends in the hope it might inspire others to wonderful things.

http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/how-you-ever-start-saying-5075533
